If the document contains any content that causes SAX to call the
ContentHandler.warning(), an exception will be thrown aborting
the construction of the document.  

The problem is in  org/apache/batik/dom/util/SAXDocumentFactory, line 383

    public void warning(SAXParseException ex) throws SAXException {
	    throw ex;
    }

The "throw ex;" should be removed leaving warning() as a NOP.
